# [Tensorflow](https://www.tensorflow.org/js) [metaframe](https://metapages.org/) for training models and getting predictions


This is a functional **versioned** [metaframe](https://metapages.org/) website with matching [npm module](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@metapages/metaframe-tensorflow-1d).

 - `Metaframe:` [https://metapages.github.io/metaframe-tensorflow-1d/](https://metapages.github.io/metaframe-tensorflow-1d/)
 - `Versioned metaframe` e.g 0.3.0: [https://metapages.github.io/metaframe-tensorflow-1d/v0.3.0/](https://metapages.github.io/metaframe-tensorflow-1d/v0.3.0/)
 - `npm module` (matches browser version): [https://www.npmjs.com/package/@metapages/metaframe-tensorflow-1d](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@metapages/metaframe-tensorflow-1d)

Inputs:

 - [training](https://github.com/metapages/metaframe-tensorflow-1d/blob/95bb75de06b8529faae6f31283efc4ecbb0fbf48/src/lib/metaframe.ts#L101)
 - [prediction](https://github.com/metapages/metaframe-tensorflow-1d/blob/95bb75de06b8529faae6f31283efc4ecbb0fbf48/src/lib/metaframe.ts#L16)
 - [model](https://github.com/metapages/metaframe-tensorflow-1d/blob/95bb75de06b8529faae6f31283efc4ecbb0fbf48/src/lib/types.ts#L46)

Outputs:

 - `error`: json
 - [prediction](https://github.com/metapages/metaframe-tensorflow-1d/blob/95bb75de06b8529faae6f31283efc4ecbb0fbf48/src/lib/metaframe.ts#L82)
 - [model](https://github.com/metapages/metaframe-tensorflow-1d/blob/95bb75de06b8529faae6f31283efc4ecbb0fbf48/src/lib/types.ts#L46)


Input a list of training data consisting of n-1-dimensional series (e.g. a bunch of time series) and this will train a model:

[![](https://mermaid.-)](https://mermaid-js.github.io/mermaid-live-editor/edit#-)


Format of training examples:

```json
{
    "examples": [
        {
            "label": "label1",
            "data": {
                "series": {
                    "series1": "base64-encoded-array-of-float32",
                    "series2": "base64-encoded-array-of-float32",
                    "seriesn": "base64-encoded-array-of-float32"
                }
            }
        },
        {
            "label": "label2",
            "data": {
                "series": {
                    "series1": "base64-encoded-array-of-float32",
                    "series2": "base64-encoded-array-of-float32",
                    "seriesn": "base64-encoded-array-of-float32"
                }
            }
        }
    ]
}

```

If there is an error (you also might see it in the metaframe itself):

[![](https://mermaid.-)](https://mermaid-js.github.io/mermaid-live-editor/edit#-)

The model will also be cached locally, so if the *same* training data is sent (compared via hashes) then the cached model will be returned, avoiding recomputing the model again.

A model can also be just passed in via the `model` input (same format as the output).

Once a model is loaded or computed, you can pass a prediction in, and get a prediction result out:

[![](https://mermaid.)](https://mermaid-js.github.io/mermaid-live-editor/edit#)


Example prediction input:

```json
{
    "series": {
        "series1": "base64-encoded-array-of-float32",
        "series2": "base64-encoded-array-of-float32",
        "seriesn": "base64-encoded-array-of-float32"
    }
}

```

Example prediction output:

```json
{
  "prediction": "label2",
  "predictions": { "label2": 0.94, "label1": 0.1, "labeln": 0.3 }
}

```
